    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>orange[s]</strong> in half, then cut half the orange into 1 <strong>orange wedge </strong>per person</p><p>Strip your <strong>coriander leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop the <strong>stalks</strong> finely, then roughly chop the <strong>leaves</strong> and keep separate</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the juice of the<strong> remaining orange </strong>(save the wedge[s] for garnish!) to a small bowl with your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> chopped coriander stalks </strong>(you'll use the leaves later!), <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Mix until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>mojo-style marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>red onion </strong>and <strong>sliced pepper</strong> to one side of a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!)<strong> </strong>and place your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> in the centre of the foil</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Pour the <strong>mojo-style marinade</strong> over the fish, then scrunch the edges of the foil together around the fish to form a tightly sealed parcel[s]</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> foil parcel[s]</strong> to the other side of the baking tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the fish is cooked through and the onion has softened \u2013 this is your <strong>Cuban-style mojo fish &</strong> <strong>roast veg</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your<strong> black beans</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained black beans</strong> to the cooked rice with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander leaves </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and cook over a medium-low heat for 1-2 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>black bean & coriander rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cuban-style-mojo-cod-with-black-bean-and-coriander-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>black bean & coriander rice</strong> and<strong> roast veg</strong> topped with the <strong>Cuban-style mojo fish</strong></p><p>Drizzle the remaining <strong>cooking juices</strong> from the foil parcel[s] over the fish</p><p>Garnish with an <strong>orange wedge</strong> and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
